; classifier-eval.form — TEST a classifier against known-correct labels; pass only on a proven bar.
;
; THE ASK:
;   Before the body routes on a perception, it must EARN that trust. self-grounding-classifier
;   promotes our own seeing by counting agreement with a route we already trust. But promotion
;   needs a measurement, and the measurement must be as honest as the gate it feeds: count what
;   the classifier got RIGHT against held-out truth, count what it got WRONG, and pass only on a
;   bar that compares exact integers — no asserted accuracy, no float ratio the kernels round apart.
;
; THE SHAPE  (runnable: form-stdlib/classifier-eval.fk · proven: tests/classifier-eval-band.fk -> 63)
;
;   A pair = (list predicted actual): what the classifier said, what the label says, for one input.
;   A set is a list of pairs — the held-out evaluation record.
;   1. HIT  ce-hit?: one pair is correct when predicted str_eq actual (1), else 0.
;   2. COUNT  ce-correct / ce-wrong / ce-total: fold the set by recursion — ce-correct sums the
;      hits, ce-wrong sums the misses, ce-total is the set size. No subtraction: wrong is counted
;      directly, never derived as total-minus-correct, so the two counts are independently true.
;   3. PASS GATE  ce-passes?: the classifier passes only when it cleared enough correct AND stayed
;      under the wrong ceiling — (and (ge correct min-correct) (ge max-wrong wrong)). Division-free:
;      ge on integers, the same verdict on Go=Rust=TS. This is the measurement self-grounding's
;      promotion gate consumes — the same bar shape, here turned outward onto a labeled test.
;
; WHY DIVISION-FREE:
;   an accuracy ratio (correct/total) is a float, and eq on floats drifts between kernels — the
;   three-way proof would diverge on rounding alone. A proven-count bar (min-correct, max-wrong)
;   carries the same intent — "right enough, wrong rarely enough" — in integers the kernels compare
;   exactly. The gate is honest in the same way value-execution.fk is: it credits only what's proven,
;   never an asserted number, and silence (a fail) below the bar is whole, never a fabricated pass.
;
; KIN — this composes the spine, it does not invent a new primitive:
;   recognition-router.form (route among model-carriers — what gets tested before it routes) ·
;   self-grounding-perception.form / self-grounding-classifier.fk (the promotion this measurement
;   feeds — same (predicted/our, actual/truth) pair shape, same division-free bar) ·
;   shared-sensing.form (the circle that confirms when no single label-set is enough) ·
;   declared-source.form (every count traces to a witnessed pair, never an assumed one).
;
; HONEST LANE / CAVEAT:
;   the verdict is exactly as honest as the labels. ce-passes? proves the classifier matched the
;   ACTUAL column on this held-out set — not that the labels are right, and not that an unseen
;   sample will hold. A passing set is grounds to PROMOTE (let self-grounding route on its own),
;   not a claim of universal accuracy. min-correct / max-wrong are the encoder's bar; raising them
;   is how the body asks for more proof before it trusts its own seeing.
